To carry out the estimation step, we utilised linear regression within both the frequentist and Bayesian frameworks. Specifically, we will run three regression models:

-   `Model.1` will include only window $(\text{W})$ as predictor;
-   `Model.2` will include window $(\text{W})$ and daylight $(\text{D})$ as predictors.
-   `Model.3` will include window $(\text{W})$ and visual comfort $(\text{V})$ as predictors.

The results of the fitted statistical models (i.e., `Model.1`, `Model.2` and `Model.3`) are presented here.

#### Frequentist framework




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
#Fit the linear regression model with W and P (Model 1)
ex3_Model.1 <-
  lm(formula = P ~ W,
     data = ex3_sample.random)
#View of the model summary
