The `coverage` is defined by setting its value to `1` if the confidence interval overlaps the data-generating parameter for `interaction` (i.e., `b_win = 0.5`) and `0` otherwise.




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
#Calculate coverage
coefs_ex3 <-
  coefs_ex3 %>%
  mutate(coverage = case_when(CI_2.5 > b_win | CI_97.5 < b_win ~ 0,
                              CI_2.5 <= b_win & CI_97.5 >= b_win ~ 1,
                              .default = NA))
#View the data frame
coefs_ex3
